Plot Output

You can also embed plots, for example:

Code 
library(ggplot2)
dat <- data.frame(cond = rep(c("A", "B"), each=10),
                  xvar = 1:20 + rnorm(20,sd=3),
                  yvar = 1:20 + rnorm(20,sd=3))

ggplot(dat, aes(x=xvar, y=yvar)) +
    geom_point(shape=1) + 
    geom_smooth()

Note that the code-fold: true parameter was added to the code chunk to hide the code by default (click âCodeâ above the plot to see the code).

The use of the label and fig-cap options make this a cross-referenceable figure (see FigureÂ 1).

Interactivity

You can also add interactive plots. For example:

Code 
library(dygraphs)
dygraph(nhtemp) %>% 
  dyRangeSelector(dateWindow = c("1920-01-01", "1960-01-01"))

Tables

Use the knitr::kable() function to print tables as HTML:

Code 
knitr::kable(head(ggplot2::diamonds))

LaTeX Math

You can also include LaTeX math:

P\left(A=2\middle|\frac{A^2}{B}>4\right)
